50|$|Chloral betaine (USAN, BAN) (brand names Beta-Chlor, Somilan), {{also known}} as <b>cloral</b> <b>betaine</b> (INN), is a sedative-hypnotic drug. It was {{introduced}} by Mead Johnson in the United States in 1963. It is a betaine complex with chloral hydrate, which acts as an extended-acting formulation of chloral hydrate which is then metabolized into trichloroethanol, {{which is responsible for}} most or all of its effects.|$|E

